### Key Findings

- **Bug**: `ssh-keyscan -H` hashes hostnames in `known_hosts` — the plain-text IP `100.120.193.82` never appears in the file
- **False failure**: `grep -q "100.120.193.82" ~/.ssh/known_hosts` always fails even when ssh-keyscan succeeds, triggering the error message
- **Fix**: Replace the grep check with `[ -s ~/.ssh/known_hosts ]` (non-empty file test) in both occurrences (lines 43 and 143 of `staging-pipeline.yml`)
- **Evidence**: CI logs show `ssh-keyscan` received valid responses (`SSH-2.0-OpenSSH_9.6p1`) before the false-positive error

