## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #653 - CI broken on main: Deploy to staging
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Every push to main is blocked — no staging or production deploys possible |
| Complexity | LOW | One-line fix in 2 identical places in a single workflow file |
| Confidence | HIGH | CI log proves host is reachable; grep failure is unambiguous due to `-H` hashing |

### Root Cause

`ssh-keyscan -H` hashes hostnames in `known_hosts` (entries look like `|1|<salt>|<hash>`), but the check `grep -q "100.120.193.82"` searches for the plain IP — which is never present. The fix is to use `ssh-keygen -F 100.120.193.82` which correctly handles hashed entries.

### Files to Modify

| File | Lines | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml` | 43 | Replace `grep -q "100.120.193.82"` with `ssh-keygen -F 100.120.193.82 -f ~/.ssh/known_hosts > /dev/null 2>&1` |
| `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml` | 143 | Same fix in `deploy-production` job |

